               Iceles, in a browniſh fleſh colour cloſe to him, like
the naked, a red mantle, great Bats wings on his ſhoulders;
on his head a bend ſet with flames.

The ſong being ended, the Maſquers came downe
from their ſeat into the roome and made their entry,
betwixt this and the ſecond dance was this ſong.
